    <text>
        <body>
            <p rend="indent(8)">
                <placeName>Cincinnati</placeName>
                <date>Jany 10. 1864</date>
            </p>
            <p>The <sic><addressee>Revd. I Leesor</addressee></sic></p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">Dr. Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">Herewith I tend the enclosed for publication<lb/> If you
                    <sic>aprove</sic> of the subject, I should like it printed soon. If it is too
                great<lb/> a length, I would sooner wait an opportunity, or have <add>it</add> laid
                on one side rather<lb/>
                <hi rend="underline">have it continued</hi>, I am now in my 74th year and wish with
                others to<lb/> put our sentiments on record, to show our <sic>sucessors</sic>, that
                although living<lb/> in the Centre of the reformers, we are the avowed enemy to
                    <sic>there</sic> Bankrupt<lb/> adventures and their actions. I have confined
                myself to facts and if they<lb/> are not ashamed of their <del>open</del> conduct I
                need neither to be afraid or ashamed to<lb/> publish them. The article at the
                    <sic>botom</sic> of page no 2. refers to the death<lb/> of <persName>Dr. D I
                    Gans</persName>, the first intemation I had of it was, the <sic>anounce</sic> of
                his death and<lb/> the funeral service from his late residence (in the <hi
                    rend="underline">Commercial</hi>)</p>
            <p>our Rabbi's advised this, because he had of late <sic>tenderd</sic> his
                    <add>professional</add> services at<lb/> our Hospital, but <add>for</add> this
                service he obtained a very considerable practice<lb/> among our own people „our by
                laws have assigned a <hi rend="underline">place</hi> in our <sic>cemetry</sic><lb/>
                for suicides—and for those marrying out of the pale of Judaism, they<lb/> can have
                no claim for interment on any account. I have <sic>carefuly</sic><lb/> read the
                action of the Board of Delegates and I would prefer, that<lb/> you give it a better
                Version than I have been able to do. I hope<lb/> you will be kind enough and correct
                the errors which are many<lb/> when this is printed please to let my number be
                accompanied with<lb/> 4 more <sic>copys</sic>. If the radicals in our midst were as
                numerous as<lb/> they are wealthy, the Temple scheme would be soon in operation<lb/>
                still it is hard to say what <del>Gold</del> Gold cannot accomplish</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I have collected Material for a continuation <del>of</del> on the
                Temple<lb/> Mania, and particularly on the subject of seating the sexes<lb/> in the
                Synagogue which I will forward soon</p>
            <p rend="indent(7)">I am</p>
            <p rend="indent(8)">D. Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(9)">Yours Truly</p>
            <p rend="indent(9)">
                <persName role="author">Saml. L. Bruel</persName>
            </p>
        </body>
